    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>LEAD: Taiwan is set to further relax its foreign-exchange controls early next year, the Central Bank Governor said. Chang Chi-Cheng, the governor, told reporters on Wednesday that the bank was revising some existing foreign-exchange regulations with the aim of further easing the way that Taiwan companies and individuals could make investments overseas.</p>
